-- 1. [Problem Restatement] Given x + 1/y = 4, y + 1/z = 1, z + 1/x = 7/3 with x,y,z > 0, find xyz. 2. [Key Idea] Multiply the three equations, expand once, and use the sum of the given equalities to isolate the symmetric expression xyz + 1/(xyz). 3. [Proof] Let P = xyz > 0. Multiply the three equations: (x + 1/y)(y + 1/z)(z + 1/x) = 4 · 1 · 7/3 = 28/3. (1) Expand the left–hand side once: (x + 1/y)(y + 1/z)(z + 1/x) = xyz + (x + y + z) + (1/x + 1/y + 1/z) + 1/(xyz). (2) Add the original equations: (x + 1/y) + (y + 1/z) + (z + 1/x) = 4 + 1 + 7/3 = 22/3, so x + y + z + 1/x + 1/y + 1/z = 22/3. (3) Substituting (3) into (2) and equating with (1): P + 1/P + 22/3 = 28/3 ⇒ P + 1/P = 2. (4) Because P > 0, equation (4) yields P^2 − 2P + 1 = 0 ⇒ (P − 1)^2 = 0 ⇒ P = 1. (5) Hence xyz = 1. 4. [Conclusion] The product xyz equals 1, so the answer is (B).
